  "riddle": "1. Seek the steed named after a Greek figure, whose racing prowess garnered numerous victories—how many wins did this gallant horse achieve?\n\n2. A geographical marvel bears the name of this champion. What is the elevation, in meters, of the place from which he hails?\n\n3. In the realm of modern reviews, how do visitors score this noble name on the stars? \n\n4. Combine the elevation you discovered in clue 2 with the rating from clue 3. What total emerges from this unison?\n\n5. Venture now to a historic event that marked the beginning of a legendary race — in what year was this significant event first held?\n\n6. The town where the next legendary races take place offers a certain height above sea level. What is that elevation in meters for the venue situated in Sunbury-on-Thames?\n\n7. Consider the elevation from clue 6. Which prime number follows it, standing resolutely as the next in line?\n\n8. Journey onwards to a tale of a horse whose name echoes the past—what country claims this strapping runner as its own? \n\n9. Time travels from a historic starting line in 1875 to a future date. How many days are there from then to March 15, 2026?\n\n10. Now compute the final puzzle: take the absolute difference between the wins from clue 1 and the rating from clue 3, as well as the year from clue 5 and the elevation from clue 6. What does the operation abs(14 - 5) modulo 10 yield? Here, your key numbers come from clues 1, 3, 5, and 6, revealing a singular digit between 0 and 9.",
